////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


// Transparent smoke surface hook fragment. Demonstrates a per-material color transform expressed as a hook (not
// a compile-time variant): the base color is square-root transformed and warm-tinted. The cook wraps it with the
// engine pixel-shader authoring + this material's typed .bind to generate the G-buffer pixel shader.
#include "smoke_material_color.slangi"


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


NwbMeshSurface nwbMaterialSurface(){
    const NwbMeshInstanceData instance = nwbMeshLoadInstance();
    const NwbSmokeSurfaceMaterial surface = nwbMaterialBindLoadSurface(instance);
    const NwbSmokeRuntimeMaterial runtime = nwbMaterialBindLoadRuntime(instance);
    const half4 tinted = half4(surface.base_color * runtime.color_tint);
    const half3 baseColor = nwbSmokeMaterialVertexColor(tinted.rgb);
    // The hook supplies only the optical PARAMS; the ENGINE integrates the shadow visibility over the true
    // entry->exit volume path (per-crossing Fresnel + signed Beer-Lambert optical depth), since only the trace sees
    // both faces of an occluder. ior 1.5 = glass (Fresnel); transmission is the per-unit absorption color, tracking
    // the per-cube tint so the cast shadow matches the base color. alpha (the AVBOIT opacity all three passes read)
    // is still hook-decided. The base color stays the rasterized appearance (the G-buffer discards ior/transmission
    // + alpha). Hardcoded test values; the production path authors them as typed .bind constants.
    NwbMeshSurface result = nwbMakeMeshSurface(baseColor, inNormal, half(0.0), half(0.0));
    result.ior = 1.5;
    result.transmission = saturate(tinted.rgb) * half(0.7);
    result.alpha = half(1.0 - nwbLuminance(result.transmission));
    return result;
}


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
